                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;&quot;You cannot un-decorate a function.&quot; - While normally true, it is possible to reach inside the closure in the function return by a decorator (i.e. via its &lt;code&gt;__closure__&lt;/code&gt; attribute) to pull out the original undecorated function.  One example usage is documented in &lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/a/33254457/2904896&quot;&gt;this answer&lt;/a&gt; which covers how it is possible to inject a decorator function in a lower level in limited circumstances.&lt;/span&gt;

