                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;functools.wraps sets the attribute &lt;code&gt;__wrapped__&lt;/code&gt; on the wrapper function, to allow retrieving the original wrapped function.  Thats more reliable than looking at closed-over variables.&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/821378/merwok&quot; title=&quot;6,637 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;merwok&lt;/a&gt;
                &lt;/div&gt;
                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-date&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;a class=&quot;comment-link&quot; href=&quot;#comment124101829_1594484&quot;&gt;&lt;span title=&quot;2021-12-02 17:22:17Z, License: CC BY-SA 4.0&quot; class=&quot;relativetime-clean&quot;&gt;Dec 2, 2021 at 17:22&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;
