            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Although this answer has the great advantage of only using the stdlib, and works for this simple example where there are no &lt;i&gt;decorator&lt;/i&gt; arguments nor &lt;i&gt;decorated function&lt;/i&gt; arguments, it has 3 major limitations: (1) no simple support for optional decorator arguments (2) not signature-preserving (3) no simple way to extract a named argument from &lt;code&gt;*args&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;**kwargs&lt;/code&gt;.  An easy way to solve these 3 issues at once is to use &lt;code&gt;decopatch&lt;/code&gt; as explained &lt;a href=&quot;https://stackoverflow.com/a/55105198/7262247&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;. You can also use &lt;code&gt;decorator&lt;/code&gt; as already mentioned by Marius Gedminas, to solve points 2 and 3.&lt;/span&gt;

